Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria, Godwin Emefiele, has laughed off the anxiety associated with his presidential ambition ahead of the 2023 general elections, saying he is having fun. Emefiele stated this while briefing journalists at the presidential villa after visiting President Muhammadu Buhari. Also Read: [BREAKING] 2023: Buhari Orders Emefiele, Other Appointees To Resign He said, “There is no news but there will be news.” When journalists inquired to know his views about the anxiety created by his ambition, the apex bank governor said: “Let them have a heart attack. It is good to have a heart attack. I am having a lot of fun.”